<instructions>
Write a professional yet approachable email to your team about the Q3 roadmap slipping by 3 weeks due to a vendor delay. Avoid blaming the vendor or any team members. Clearly communicate what is changing and what remains the same. Mention that there is a mitigation plan in place, but the details are not finalized yet. Maintain a tone that is professional but not overly corporate or stiff.
</instructions>

<examples>
Example email excerpt:
"Hi team, I want to update you on our Q3 roadmap. Due to an unexpected vendor delay, our timeline will shift by approximately three weeks. While this impacts some deliverables, other key milestones remain on track. We have a mitigation plan underway, and I will share more details once finalized. Thank you for your continued focus and flexibility."
</examples>

<success_criteria>
- The email clearly states the 3-week delay in the Q3 roadmap caused by a vendor delay without assigning blame.
- The tone is professional but friendly and not overly formal or stiff.
- The email specifies what aspects of the roadmap are changing and what remains unchanged.
- It mentions a mitigation plan exists but that details are still being finalized.
</success_criteria>

Confirm the email meets every success criterion before finishing.